	<Title>
		Recipe: Blue cheese, walnut spinach salad
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Blue cheese, walnut spinach salad &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		12
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a gluten-free recipe.
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Combine ingredients for dressing in a blender or processor. Chill. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Toss spinach greens with dressing and mound a generous 1 cup onto chilled plates. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Layer vegetables, walnuts and blue cheese crumbles on top of spinach. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Serve. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;
Dressing 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4 teaspoons olive oil&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon maple syrup&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 teaspoon nutmeg&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;3 teaspoons plain low-fat yogurt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 pounds spinach, roughly chopped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup sliced red onion&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cups sliced cucumbers&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cups grape tomatoes&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup walnuts, chopped&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup blue cheese crumbles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
